{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":863,"record_hash":"sha256:4ea79c1b78e85ff4044501afd8e98145bc24eeaebfde85f49c93aa7f6bdf14ab","timestamp":"2026-05-07T11:34:43.139Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"user","text":"<subagent_notification>\n{\"agent_path\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"status\":{\"completed\":\"**Findings**\\n\\n::code-comment{title=\\\"[P1] Dry run creates GitMeta state\\\" body=\\\"`write_capture()` opens `git_meta_lib::Session` before checking `plan.dry_run`, and that open path creates `.git/git-meta.sqlite`. This violates the request contract that dry-run plans without writing GitMeta state; I confirmed with a temp repo that `--dry-run` leaves `git-meta-db=present`. Use a non-creating/read-only store path for dry runs, or skip GitMeta when no store exists and treat prior hashes as empty.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-capture/src/gitmeta.rs\\\" start=44 end=59 priority=1 confidence=0.94}\\n\\n::code-comment{title=\\\"[P2] New dependency duplicates Gitoxide stack\\\" body=\\\"The workspace adds `git-meta-lib` as a pinned Git dependency, and `but-capture` depends on it directly. The lockfile shows `git-meta-lib` pulling crates.io `gix 0.81.0` while the workspace already uses pinned Gitoxide `gix 0.83.0`, duplicating a large family of `gix-*` crates under `but --features capture`. Align `git-meta-lib` to the workspace Gitoxide revision, vendor/path it, or hide it behind a narrow adapter until dependency policy is settled.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/Cargo.toml\\\" start=210 priority=2 confidence=0.91}\\n\\n::code-comment{title=\\\"[P2] In-batch duplicate records are not deduped\\\" body=\\\"`compute_write_plan()` checks every record only against the pre-existing GitMeta hash sets. If the same source JSON line appears twice in one transcript, both copies are planned as new; metadata counts/bytes are overreported and transcript capture appends duplicate envelopes before the set catches up. Clone the seen sets into mutable planned sets and insert each accepted hash as the plan is built.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-capture/src/gitmeta.rs\\\" start=105 end=118 priority=2 confidence=0.86}\\n\\n::code-comment{title=\\\"[P2] Final malformed JSON is always ignored\\\" body=\\\"The parser skips any malformed last non-empty record, regardless of whether the file ended with a newline or whether the serde error was actually EOF. That can silently drop a corrupt completed transcript. Only tolerate a final partial record when the parse error is EOF and the snapshot lacks a terminating newline, or expose an explicit lenient/live-tail mode.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-capture/src/transcript.rs\\\" start=27 end=31 priority=2 confidence=0.9}\\n\\n::code-comment{title=\\\"[P2] Path identity is lossy\\\" body=\\\"The canonical transcript path is converted with `to_string_lossy()` and then used both for persisted metadata and as the fallback session-key hash input. On Unix, distinct non-UTF-8 paths can collapse through replacement characters, causing wrong keys or misleading stored paths. Hash platform-native path bytes for identity and keep lossy strings only for display, or fail explicitly on non-UTF-8 if GitMeta requires UTF-8.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-capture/src/capture.rs\\\" start=107 priority=2 confidence=0.82}\\n\\n::code-comment{title=\\\"[P3] Public error/API surface is not ready\\\" body=\\\"`CaptureError` loses actionable context for unreadable paths, malformed JSON, and cwd mismatches, while also exposing `git_meta_lib::Error` in the public API. That makes CLI/API callers match poor strings or depend on the GitMeta implementation. Prefer owned variants with path/line/source fields and keep `git-meta-lib` behind crate-private conversion; also consider taking `Agent` rather than raw `String` in `CaptureRequest`.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-capture/src/capture.rs\\\" start=50 end=70 priority=3 confidence=0.88}\\n\\n::code-comment{title=\\\"[P3] Exemplary placement lacks doc gate\\\" body=\\\"The workspace places `but-capture` in the 'Exemplary' section, whose comment calls for exhaustive docs via `#![deny(missing_docs)]`, but the crate has no crate-level docs or missing-docs gate and re-exports public types immediately. Either add the doc gate and public API docs now, or classify the POC under Needs Work until the API settles.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/Cargo.toml\\\" start=8 end=24 priority=3 confidence=0.93}\\n\\nI did not find direct `gitbutler-*`, `but-api`, `but-ctx`, `git2`, or `VirtualBranchesHandle` usage inside `crates/but-capture`; the legacy-boundary concern is mainly the new `git-meta-lib` integration and its dependency graph.\\n\\nValidation run: `cargo check -p but-capture --all-targets`, `cargo clippy -p but-capture --all-targets --no-deps`, `cargo test -p but-capture`, `cargo check -p but --features capture --no-default-features`, and `cargo check -p but --features capture` all passed.\"}}\n</subagent_notification>","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-07T11:34:43.139Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"user","content":[{"type":"input_text","text":"<subagent_notification>\n{\"agent_path\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"status\":{\"completed\":\"**Findings**\\n\\n::code-comment{title=\\\"[P1] Dry run creates GitMeta state\\\" body=\\\"`write_capture()` opens `git_meta_lib::Session` before checking `plan.dry_run`, and that open path creates `.git/git-meta.sqlite`. This violates the request contract that dry-run plans without writing GitMeta state; I confirmed with a temp repo that `--dry-run` leaves `git-meta-db=present`. Use a non-creating/read-only store path for dry runs, or skip GitMeta when no store exists and treat prior hashes as empty.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-capture/src/g